2. `tocloft` is the package used to customize the appearance of the table of contents. It is loaded using the `\usepackage` command.
3. `\frontmatter` and `\backmatter` are environment commands that separate the front matter (title page, abstract, etc.) and back matter (bibliography, appendices, etc.) from the main content.
4. `\pagestyle{plain}` sets the page style to plain (i.e., no headers or footers).
5. `\tableofcontents` generates the table of contents, which is automatically created based on the content structure of the document.
6. The `\chapter` and `\section` commands define the chapter and section titles, respectively.
7. The TOC is generated automatically based on these chapter and section definitions.

